{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"padding","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"edges","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge","text":"Edge","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","text":"Set","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO3SetV"},{"text":" = .all, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"length","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGFloat","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"edges","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The set of edges to pad for this view. The default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set\/all","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"length","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An amount, given in points, to pad this view on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified edges. If you set the value to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", OpenSwiftUI uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a platform-specific default amount. The default value of this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that’s padded by the specified amount on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified edges."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this modifier to add a specified amount of padding to one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edges of the view. Indicate the edges to pad by naming either a single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value from "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", or by specifying an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/Swift\/OptionSet","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contains edge values:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text padded by 20 points on the bottom and trailing edges.\")","        .padding([.bottom, .trailing], 20)","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The order in which you apply modifiers matters. The example above"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applies the padding before applying the border to ensure that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"border encompasses the padded region:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can omit either or both of the parameters. If you omit the ","type":"text"},{"code":"length","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"OpenSwiftUI uses a default amount of padding. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"omit the ","type":"text"},{"code":"edges","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", OpenSwiftUI applies the padding to all edges. Omit both","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to add a default padding all the way around a view. OpenSwiftUI chooses a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default amount of padding that’s appropriate for the platform and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the presentation context.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text with default padding.\")","        .padding()","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above looks like this in iOS under typical conditions:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To control the amount of padding independently for each edge, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/padding(_:)-6pgqq"},{"type":"text","text":". To pad all outside edges of a view by a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified amount, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/padding(_:)-68shk"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds an equal padding amount to specific edges of this view."}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/capsule\/padding(_:_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method",